      appointed” to God’s wrath.  Verse 9 is also used by those who teach a pretribulation rapture.  Both this verse and
      1 st Thess.1:10 are taken out of context by the dispensationalist.  The truth that the wicked will receive
      punishment while the righteous will receive rewards at Jesus’ second coming is a theme that is repeatedly taught in
      the scriptures.
    </p>
    <p><b>
      “And to you who are troubled rest with us, when the Lord Jesus shall be revealedfrom heaven with his mighty
      angels.
      In flaming fire taking vengence on them that know not God, and that obey not the gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ:
